webpackJsonp([0xc9cf82aea717d000],{"./node_modules/json-loader/index.js!./.cache/json/miscellaneous-dynamic-urls-using-routeparams-in-angular.json":function(e,a){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p>What if you have a lot of users posting <em>things</em> to your website? Maybe your users want to have a profile, or a wall, of the <em>things</em> they’ve posted, and they want to be able to share it with their friends with a url? You can do that, no biggie!</p>\n<p>Let’s say you used</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-none"><code>>> yo angular-fullstack:route wall</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>to generate a <a><a href="http://myapp.wherever.com/wall/">http://myapp.wherever.com/wall/</a></a> route for your users. You want a link to <a><a href="http://myapp.wherever.com/wall/someUsername">http://myapp.wherever.com/wall/someUsername</a></a> to show a specific user’s <em>things</em>.<br>\nBrowse to <strong>/client/app/wall/wall.js</strong> and notice that it detects what URL the user is requesting before acting on it:</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-none"><code>$routeProvider.when(\'/wall\', …</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>You can customize that path to catch when a user is trying to see a profile associated with a specific username like so:</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-none"><code>$routeProvider.when(\'/wall/:username\', …</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>The colon before “username” indicates that this is a variable, which is then passed to the <em>$routeParams</em> module. In <strong>wall.controller.js</strong>, include <em>$routeParams</em>:</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-none"><code>.controller(\'WallCtrl\', function ($scope, $routeParams) { …</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>Then later on in <strong>wall.controller.js</strong>, you can see what username was requested in the URL by referring to the variable generated by <em>$routeProvider</em> using something like</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-none"><code>var wallOwner = $routeParams.username;</code></pre>\n      </div>',fields:{slug:"/miscellaneous/dynamic-urls-using-routeparams-in-angular/"},frontmatter:{title:"Dynamic Urls Using Routeparams in Angular"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/miscellaneous/dynamic-urls-using-routeparams-in-angular/"}}}});
